<title>INDIA: Wellcome (India) 96 net profit at 95.4 mln rupees.</title>
<headline>Wellcome (India) 96 net profit at 95.4 mln rupees.</headline>
<dateline>BOMBAY 1997-02-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year ending December 31, 1996</p>
<p>	     (in million rupees unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net profit		95.40	vs	-35.76</p>
<p>    Net sales	    1,842.29	vs    1,090.18</p>
<p>    Profit before tax    163.40	vs	-35.76</p>
<p>    Other income	    91.13	vs	 25.41</p>
<p>    Expenditure	  1,717.28	vs    1,101.51</p>
<p>    Interest		  39.81	vs	 41.03</p>
<p>    Gross profit	   176.32	vs	-26.95</p>
<p>    Depreciation	    12.91	vs	  8.80</p>
<p>    Tax			 68.0	 vs	   Nil</p>
<p>Note: Burroughs Wellcome (India), a subsidiary of Glaxo Wellcome Plc of U.K. said the year-ago figures were for the 9 months from April 1995 to December 1995.</p>
<p>The company attributed the turnaround to 26.7 percent sales growth over the year-ago period on an annualised basis, operational efficiencies, cost control and better working capital management.</p>
<p>Burroughs Wellcome said the firm's paid-up capital stood at 91.76 million rupees against 74.96 million in the year-ago period.</p>
<p>-- Bombay newsroom +91-22-265 9000</p>
